Cutar HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta samu karuwar sabbin masu cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na mutanen da ke dauke da cutar kanjamau.
"Mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a kasar", in ji wakilin kiwon lafiya.
An samu sabbin mutane kusan dubu 40 a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka suna faruwa ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ke nuna canji daga baya.
A al'adance, cutar HIV ta yadu cikin sauri a wasu sassan kasar Sin ta hanyar kamuwa da cutar ta hanyar jini.
Amma adadin mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar ya kusan zuwa sifili, in ji wani jami'in kiwon lafiya a kasar Sin a wani taro da aka yi a lardin Yunnan.
Duk da haka, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke fama da cutar kanjamau a China ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Yaduwar cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An haramta luwadi a kasar Sin a shekarar 1997, amma ana nuna bambanci ga LGBT.
Saboda dabi'un kasar masu ra'ayin mazan jiya, an kiyasta cewa kashi 70-90 cikin dari na maza da ke yin jima'i da maza, suna yin aure da mata.
Yawancin cututtuka suna faruwa ne saboda rashin isasshen kariya ta jima'i a cikin waɗannan yanayi.
Tun daga 2003, hukumomin kasar Sin sun yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar HIV ga kowa a kasar.
