Ambasadoran Amurka ya zargi China da cin zarafin 'yan kasar ta ta hanyar tallata tallace-tallace
Mako guda bayan da wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wata sanarwa mai shafuka hudu a wata jaridar Amurka da ke nuna fa'idodin kasuwanci tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da jaridar Amurka don yada farfaganda.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi nuni a ranar Laraba ga wani shafi da jaridar China Daily ta biya don shiga cikin jaridar Des Moines Register  jaridar da ta fi sayarwa a Iowa  bayan da ta zargi China da kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, zargin da China ta yi watsi da shi.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin yin tasiri a zaben Amurka, ya nuna wani sabon mataki a yakin da Washington ke yi na matsa wa China lamba, in ji jami'an Amurka a cewar Reuters.
Ko da yake al'ada ce hukumomin kasashen waje su rika amfani da tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, amma Beijing da Washington sun shiga cikin wani rikici na cinikayya da ke kara tsanantawa da ya haifar da sabbin kudaden haraji kan kayayyakin da suke shigowa da su.
Kudin da kasar Sin ta biya a farkon yakin cinikayya ya shafi kamfanonin fitar da kayayyaki a jihohi kamar Iowa, wanda ke goyon bayan jam'iyyar Trump, in ji masana kasar Sin da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa mai shekaru da yawa wanda babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona ne zuwa China, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanoni barazana.
Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wani rubutu a cikin Des Moines Register na ranar Lahadi: "Kina yanzu tana kara tsananta wa hargitsi ta hanyar gudanar da tallace-tallace a cikin 'yan jaridarmu.
Ta hanyar yada wannan farfaganda, hukumomin kasar Sin suna amfani da 'yancin fadin albarkacin baki da kuma 'yan jarida a Amurka don sanya wani talla a cikin Des Moines Register, Branstad ya rubuta.
A matsayin bambanci  a gidan jarida a kan titin nan a Beijing ba za ka sami ra'ayoyi masu banbanci da yawa ba kuma ba za ka iya fuskantar tunani na gaske tsakanin Sinawa na yau da kullun game da matsalar tattalin arzikin kasar Sin ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin yatsan jam'iyyar kwaminis ta kasar Sin, in ji shi.
